text.section:
To carry out its purposes and in compliance with the Affordable Care Act, the Individual Exchange navigator program, with respect only to the Maryland Medical Assistance Program, the Maryland Children's Health Program, and qualified plans offered in the Exchange, shall provide comprehensive consumer assistance services, including:
conducting education and outreach to individuals;
distributing information about:
the Individual Exchange, including eligibility requirements for applicable federal premium subsidies and cost-sharing assistance;
eligibility requirements for the Maryland Medical Assistance Program and the Maryland Children's Health Program; and
procedures for enrolling in the Maryland Medical Assistance Program, the Maryland Children's Health Program, or qualified plans offered in the Individual Exchange;
with respect to qualified plans, facilitating:
plan selection, based on the needs of the individual seeking to enroll;
assessment of tax implications and premium and cost-sharing requirements; and
application, enrollment, renewal, and disenrollment processes;
facilitating eligibility determinations for the Maryland Medical Assistance Program and the Maryland Children's Health Program, selection of managed care organizations, and application, enrollment, and disenrollment processes;
conducting eligibility determinations and redeterminations for premium subsidies and cost-sharing assistance;
providing referrals to appropriate agencies, including the Attorney General's Health Education and Advocacy Unit and the Administration, for applicants and enrollees with grievances, complaints, questions, or the need for other social services;
providing all information and services in a manner that is culturally and linguistically appropriate and ensures accessibility for individuals with disabilities; and
providing ongoing support with respect to issues relating to eligibility, enrollment, renewal, and disenrollment in the Maryland Medical Assistance Program, the Maryland Children's Health Program, and qualified plans offered in the Individual Exchange.

section.section:
The Commissioner may suspend or revoke an Individual Exchange navigator entity authorization after notice and opportunity for a hearing under §§ 2-210 through 2-214 of this article if the Individual Exchange navigator entity:
has willfully violated this article or any regulation adopted under this article;
has engaged in fraudulent or dishonest practices in conducting activities under the Individual Exchange navigator entity authorization;
has had any professional license or certification suspended or revoked for a fraudulent or dishonest practice;
has been convicted of a felony, a crime of moral turpitude, or any criminal offense involving dishonesty or breach of trust; or
has willfully failed to comply with or violated a proper order or subpoena of the Commissioner.

text.section:
An Individual Exchange navigator:
shall hold an Individual Exchange navigator certification issued under subsection (j) of this section;
may provide consumer assistance services that are required to be provided by an Individual Exchange navigator under subsection (d)(1) of this section;
may not be required to hold an insurance producer or adviser license;
shall be employed or engaged by an Individual Exchange navigator entity;
shall receive compensation only through the Individual Exchange or an Individual Exchange navigator entity and not from a carrier or an insurance producer;
may not receive any compensation, directly or indirectly:
from a carrier, an insurance producer, or a third-party administrator in connection with the enrollment of a qualified individual in a qualified health plan; or
from a managed care organization that participates in the Maryland Medical Assistance Program in connection with the enrollment of an individual in the Maryland Medical Assistance Program or the Maryland Children's Health Program;
with respect to the insurance market outside the Exchange, is subject to the same requirements applicable to Individual Exchange navigator entities as set forth in subsection (f)(8) of this section; and
shall comply with all State and federal laws, regulations, and policies governing the Maryland Medical Assistance Program and the Maryland Children's Health Program.

section.section:
To qualify for an Individual Exchange navigator certification, an applicant:
shall be of good character and trustworthy;
shall be at least 18 years old;
shall complete, and comply with any ongoing requirements of, the training program established under subsection (k) of this section; and
shall comply with all applicable requirements of the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene.

The Commissioner may suspend or revoke an Individual Exchange navigator certification after notice and opportunity for a hearing under §§ 2-210 through 2-214 of this article if the certified Individual Exchange navigator:
has willfully violated this article or any regulation adopted under this article;
has intentionally misrepresented or concealed a material fact in the application for the Individual Exchange navigator certification;
has obtained the Individual Exchange navigator certification by misrepresentation, concealment, or other fraud;
has engaged in fraudulent or dishonest practices in conducting activities under the Individual Exchange navigator certification;
has misappropriated, converted, or unlawfully withheld money in conducting activities under the Individual Exchange navigator certification;
has failed or refused to pay over on demand money that belongs to a person entitled to the money;
has willfully and materially misrepresented the provisions of a qualified plan;
has been convicted of a felony, a crime of moral turpitude, or any criminal offense involving dishonesty or breach of trust;
has failed an examination required by this article or regulations adopted under this article;
has forged another's name on an application for a qualified plan or on any other document in conducting activities under the Individual Exchange navigator certification;
has otherwise shown a lack of trustworthiness or competence to act as an Individual Exchange navigator; or
has willfully failed to comply with or violated a proper order or subpoena of the Commissioner.
